Humm…possible, possible. Assuming that they don’t react odd to fire or explosions, that would work. Now, the question becomes, is it worth keeping these things around in order to research their ability? As nasty as these things are, they do allow vision into an otherwise unreachable form of sight. Find a way to use that, and it could become very useful. They’re also relatively easy to contain, just stick them in a room and don’t let people get stared at for too long. Imagine dropping a bunch of these into an enemy base…

I guess it seems like the army would want it for shock attacks, and the researchers would want it for the vision. If people vote for this to be neutralized, I’ll punch up an entry for that and change the status. I’ll watch the rating and comments, and see what people feel is the best idea.







